 Height, weight, and waist circumference (WC) were measured with the subjects in their underwear.

 Body mass index (BMI) was computed by the formula as the ratio of weight to the square of height (kg/m2).

 WC was measured on the line between the iliac crest and the lower costal margin parallel to the ground after subjects exhaled.

 Inclusion criteria of study was female patients who have over active bladder symptomes with or without urinary incontinence.

